canonical:
  title: 次安謹齋題竹院
  author: 安震
  language: lzh
  text: 西堂多後學風味亦依前挽袖爭添酒何輸昔少年
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 次安謹齋題竹院
  author: 安震
  language: lzh
  text: 西堂多後學。風味亦依前。挽袖爭添酒。何輸昔少年。
korean:
  title: 안근재의 죽원에 제한 시에 차운하여
  author: 안진
  language: kor
  text: |-
    서당에 후학이 많아
    풍미 또한 예전과 같다
    소매를 이끌어 술 권하기를 다투니
    어찌 옛 소년에게 질소냐
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_010_0310&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: In Response to An Geun-jae's Poem on the Bamboo Courtyard
  author: An Jin
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The western hall fills with eager students,
    the spirit and flavor unchanged from before.
    We tug at our sleeves, competing to pour the wine—
    how do we yield to the vigor of youth long past?
  footnotes:
    - The 'western hall' (西堂) refers to a study or scholarly retreat, suggesting a place of learning and gathering. 'Bamboo courtyard' (竹院) traditionally symbolizes scholarly refinement and virtuousness in East Asian poetry.
